Class Source

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.cep.Processor
      • ca.uqac.lif.cep.SingleProcessor

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contextualizable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MySqlSource, QueueSource, Splicer, StreamReader

    public abstract class Source
extends SingleProcessor
    Produces output events from no input. In other words, a source is a processor with input arity 0. It is the opposite of the Sink.

    While a source has no input trace, this does not mean it has not input at all. For example, a processor reading from a file and creating events out of the file's content is an example of a source. It does not receive events as input, yet creates output events from something external to it.

    Author:
    Sylvain Hallé
